The paper deals with constructing a linear code, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of LDPC codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to coding theory (cs.CR) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The application of the problem in Physical Unclonable Functions (PUFs) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer security (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
